<br>
Head: Runed Circlet<br>
Mask: Splitpaw Hide Mask<br>
Neck: Black Iron Medallion<br>
Ears: Gold Jasper Earrings x2<br>
Arms: Ulthork Hide Arms<br>
Wrists: Polished Bone Bracers x2<br>
Hands: Splitpaw Hide Gloves<br>
Finger 1: Platinum Jasper Ring<br>
Finger 2: Silver Imbued Plains Ring (I like the idea of wearing a Karana only item)<br>
Chest: Cured Tizmak Surcoat (I like the AC and resist on this piece, and it matches my Ulthork arms)<br>
Shoulders: Braided Ivy Cords<br>
Back: Kunzar Cloak<br>
Belt: Splitpaw Hide Belt<br>
Legs: Ulthork Hide Leggings<br>
Feet: Acolytes Anklet<br>
Primary: Velium Etched Stone Mace<br>
Secondary: Testament of Vanear<br>
Ranged: Kerran Toy<br>
<br>
I would like to thank everyone in advance for your help. Also since I am flat broke, does anyone know a good hunting area for making some good money and experience? Thanks again.<br>
<br>
Edit: I forgot to mention that my wis is at 163 with the above equipment, less with the Staff of the Observers<br>
<br>
Gasin Furyfoot<br>
Level 29 druid of Karana<br>
Master Baker<br>
Blades of Light<br>
Solusek Ro server <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugasinfuryfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gasin Furyfoot</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 4/20/01 7:49:13 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umicewandu02.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Micewandu02</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/21/01 8:14:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some advice from you kind Druids )</span><hr size=1> You need to dump the Ulthork/Tizmak and get some wisdom gear.  I know it looks cool and all, but that's really all it is... other than the ulthork arms, the rest of it is crap specially if you are hurting for wis gear.  For legs... get a partner and camp the ancient crocodile in upper guk for some gatorscale leggings.  I forget the AC on the legs but they are +4wis.  I think you can also do the goblin foreman in sol A and get a foremans's tunic which is +3 wis.  I'm also pretty sure you are high enough to start the Paw of Opalla quest.  I'm wondering also which race are you.. you should have much higher wisdom with the equipment you have already.  Did you put all of your points into wis when you started ??<br>
<br>
As for making money.... Furyfoot Airlines is now open.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umicewandu02.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Micewandu02</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 4/21/01 8:15:28 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umcmarcuswolfwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>McMarcus Wolfwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/22/01 7:32:45 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://my.voyager.net/~mdmckay/mch.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some advice from you kind Druids )</span><hr size=1> Here's some items that a 51 druid has... it's me if you're wondering, hehe... i'll just list the wis stats that each item has and also mana... my base wis is 115, and with equipment i have 201 wis, and an extra 195 mana in mana items... hope this gives you some ideas on what you might want to get.<br>
<br>
Name:  McMarcus Wolfwalker the Wanderer <br>
Level:  51 <br>
Class:  Druid <br>
Race:  Halfling <br>
Server:  Mithaniel Marr <br>
  <br>
Held Items &amp; Weaponry <br>
Primary (Hand/Melee):  Paw of Opolla (9wis +5mana)<br>
Secondary (Hand/Melee):  Testament of Vanear (10wis +10mana)<br>
Ranged Weapon:  Small Wisdom Deity (2wis)<br>
Ranged Ammo:  None <br>
  <br>
Armor &amp; Clothing <br>
Head:  Nightshade Wreath (5wis)<br>
Face:  Velium Ruby Veil (8wis)<br>
Chest:  Ulthork Hide Tunic (3wis +35 mana)<br>
Left Wrist:  Chipped Bone Bracelet (5wis)<br>
Right Wrist:  Chipped Bone Bracelet (5wis)<br>
Neck:  Black Sapphire Velium Necklace (65mana)<br>
Hands:  Split Paw Hide Gloves (2wis)<br>
Shoulder:  Braided Ivy Cords (5wis)<br>
Arms:  Elder Spiritist's Vambraces (free drones of doom)<br>
Waist:  Lizardscale Belt (10mana)<br>
Legs:  Kromrif Military Leggings (5wis)<br>
Feet:  Golden Efreeti Boots (9wis)<br>
Back:  Mammoth Hide Cloak (4wis)<br>
  <br>
Jewelery <br>
Left Earring:  Golden Black Sapphire Earring (35 mana)<br>
Right Earring:  Golden Black Sapphire Earring (35 mana)<br>
Left Ring:  Velium Jasper Ring (7wis)<br>
Right Ring:  Velium Jasper Ring (7wis)<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugasinfuryfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gasin Furyfoot</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/23/01 1:04:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thanks</span><hr size=1> I really appreciate your input on my dilemma. I forgot to mention that I am a Halfling. When I created my Druid, it was a long time ago, and I didnt think about putting all the points into Wis, back then I didnt think it was that important. Anyways I just got myself a Foremans Tunic hunting in SolA with my best friend who is a warrior. That was pretty easy, but the Ancient Croc in Guk is a whole different story. I do not have the time nor patience to camp that thing, not to mention he has always been camped when I was there.<br>
<br>
With all my wis boosting equipment and empty pockets buying it all, I am at 167 wis, which I dont think is bad.<br>
<br>
What about the Paw of Oppola quest? Can it be soloed at level 29? When I was in Guk asking about the AC, I found out where the mutant fungus spawns as well. How long would I need to camp it? And is it perma-camped like the AC? Thanks again.<br>
<br>
Gasin Furyfoot<br>
29th Druid of Karana<br>
Blades of Light<br>
Solusek Ro server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umcmarcuswolfwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>McMarcus Wolfwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/23/01 6:48:59 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://my.voyager.net/~mdmckay/mch.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks</span><hr size=1> At that level you might want to have help holding the camp for the fungus muntant... When I did it, I had the services of a Paladin 5 levels above me help when i was level 30.  He was able to solo the guy easy with my damage shield.  The only bad thing about the fungus muntant is that he has Clockwork poison, which makes you spin round and round and you are stunned for a bit.  He doesn't have too many hps, you just have to watch out for other fungus things healing him...  I guess it all depends, anything can drop off the muntant, most of the time we got nothing, but the second time we killed him, he dropped the rare drop, and had to wait another 3 hours before we finally got the common drop, lol.  Good luck to you and your Paw Quest :)  That was a long but fun one to do when I had my friends there during some long camps, especially for Gynok Moltor, lol.  I had to wait 9.5 hours for him to spawn.<br>
<br>
McMarcus Wolfwalker<br>
51 Wanderer of Karana<br>
Mithaniel Marr Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujarinyasinsemilia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarinya Sinsemilia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/24/01 1:32:42 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.aim.fr/gdl/pics/eq/Jarinya.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks</span><hr size=1> Even on a crowded server like Karana, the fongus is not perma-camped. When I did the quest (around 35ish level) it was easy getting the camp. But I must have camped him about 10 hours before the rare drop (Degenerated Guk Weed) And I got 3 or 4 uncommon drop from him before (cant remember the name, but its to get the copper ring).<br>
<br>
I really think the mutant room will be too tough at 29 if youre alone. You could solo it, but all the jumpers in the room will get youy killed. Be careful :)<br>
